        @Nullable
public @Nullable String getResourceBundleBaseName()
        Description copied from interface: ViolationReporter
        Get the resource bundle base name for loading the default resource bundle for this violation reporter. Returns getClass().getName() by default. If this method is overridden to return null, the oakpal framework will not attempt to load a parent resource bundle specific to this violation reporter when creating a resource bundle during initialization.
